inning.<\/p>\n<p>The company now has 13 million learners registered on its platform.<\/p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><\/td>\n<td>2017<\/td>\n<td>2018<\/td>\n<td>2019<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Courses<sup>1<\/sup><\/td>\n<td>578<\/td>\n<td>736<\/td>\n<td>883<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Programs<\/td>\n<td>13<\/td>\n<td>22<\/td>\n<td>35<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Academic Certificates<sup>2<\/sup><\/td>\n<td>7<\/td>\n<td>14<\/td>\n<td>17<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Degrees<sup>2<\/sup><\/td>\n<td>4<\/td>\n<td>18<\/td>\n<td>23<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Learners<\/td>\n<td>7.1m<\/td>\n<td>8.7m<\/td>\n<td>10m<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>Class Central interviewed Simon Nelson, back in 2015. You can read the interview here: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/futurelearn\/\">The MOOC Platform with a Twist: The Emergence of UK-Based FutureLearn<\/a><\/p>\n<p>To see how FutureLearn has evolved over the years, check out Class Central\u2019s Year in Reviews.<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/futurelearn-2019-year-review\/\">FutureLearn\u2019s 2019: Year in Review<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/futurelearn-2018-year-review\/\">FutureLearn\u2019s 2018: Year in Review<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/futurelearn-2017-year-review\/\">FutureLearn\u2019s 2017: Year in Review<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/futurelearn-2016-review\/\">FutureLearn\u2019s 2016: Year in Review<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>[1] The numbers represent the total number of courses offered in that particular year.<\/p>\n<p>[2] Graduate and Postgraduate Certificates are listed under academic certificates, instead of under degrees.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Simon Nelson has submitted his resignation as the CEO of the company, which will take effect at the end of 2020.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":72223,"comment_statu